abstract: Black neighborhoods in key swing states hold enormous power to reshape politics. Here’s an ambitious plan to maximize turnout.
snippet: Black neighborhoods in key swing states hold enormous power to reshape politics. Here’s an ambitious plan to maximize turnout.
lead_paragraph: Black neighborhoods in key swing states hold enormous power to reshape politics in November and beyond. But in order to maximize this potential, progressives need to imagine and invest on an unprecedented scale.

abstract: Most presidents avoid talking about a rising market because they know how fragile it is.
snippet: Most presidents avoid talking about a rising market because they know how fragile it is.
lead_paragraph: There’s a reason most presidents are cautious when talking about the stock market. President Trump is learning it the hard way this week.

abstract: Israel's foreign minister denounced Democratic front-runner Bernie Sanders on Wednesday for what he called his “horrifying comment" about Jerusalem, saying that those who support Israel would not back Sanders' presidential candidacy after such remarks.
snippet: Israel's foreign minister denounced Democratic front-runner Bernie Sanders on Wednesday for what he called his “horrifying comment" about Jerusalem, saying that those who support Israel would not back Sanders' presidential candidacy after such rem...
lead_paragraph: JERUSALEM — Israel's foreign minister denounced Democratic front-runner Bernie Sanders on Wednesday for what he called his “horrifying comment" about Jerusalem, saying that those who support Israel would not back Sanders' presidential candidacy after such remarks.
headline_main: Israeli Foreign Minister Slams Sanders 'Horrifying Comment'
headline_print_headline: Israeli Foreign Minister Slams Sanders 'Horrifying Comment'

abstract: India Prime Minister Narendra Modi appealed for peace in Delhi on Wednesday after days of violent clashes between Hindus and minority Muslims over a citizenship law left at least 20 people killed.
snippet: India Prime Minister Narendra Modi appealed for peace in Delhi on Wednesday after days of violent clashes between Hindus and minority Muslims over a citizenship law left at least 20 people killed.
lead_paragraph: NEW DELHI — India Prime Minister Narendra Modi appealed for peace in Delhi on Wednesday after days of violent clashes between Hindus and minority Muslims over a citizenship law left at least 20 people killed.
headline_main: Indian PM Modi Calls for Calm in Delhi After Sectarian Clashes
headline_print_headline: Indian PM Modi Calls for Calm in Delhi After Sectarian Clashes

abstract: China minted three times as many new billionaires than the United States in the past year, with fortunes made in drugs and online entertainment after a mini-boom from the coronavirus outbreak, a ranking of the world's wealthiest people shows.
snippet: China minted three times as many new billionaires than the United States in the past year, with fortunes made in drugs and online entertainment after a mini-boom from the coronavirus outbreak, a ranking of the world's wealthiest people shows.
lead_paragraph: BEIJING — China minted three times as many new billionaires than the United States in the past year, with fortunes made in drugs and online entertainment after a mini-boom from the coronavirus outbreak, a ranking of the world's wealthiest people shows.
headline_main: New Chinese Billionaires Outpace U.S. by 3 to 1: Hurun
headline_print_headline: New Chinese Billionaires Outpace U.S. by 3 to 1: Hurun

abstract: Once hailed as a national hero, Bernard Kerik was struggling for work and living on the margins of power until his friends ascended in Washington.
snippet: Once hailed as a national hero, Bernard Kerik was struggling for work and living on the margins of power until his friends ascended in Washington.
lead_paragraph: It was as if the last decade had not happened.

abstract: U.S. Attorney General William Barr warned a group of Christian broadcasters on Wednesday that the decline of religion in America is undermining liberal democracy. In a speech at the National Religious Broadcasters convention in Tennessee, Barr said religion is necessary to provide citizens with a moral compass. Without religious morality, tyranny is necessary to control people, he said.

lead_paragraph: NASHVILLE, Tenn. — U.S. Attorney General William Barr warned a group of Christian broadcasters on Wednesday that the decline of religion in America is undermining liberal democracy. In a speech at the National Religious Broadcasters convention in Tennessee, Barr said religion is necessary to provide citizens with a moral compass. Without religious morality, tyranny is necessary to control people, he said.
headline_main: Barr, DeVos Speak at Religious Broadcasters Forum
